Short Title: Satellite Annexation Cap/Rural Hall Fire Dist. (Local)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
April 22, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REMOVE THE CAP ON SATELLITE ANNEXATION FROM VARIOUS
3 MUNICIPALITIES AND TO REMOVE THE TOWN OF RURAL HALL FROM THE
4 FORSYTH COUNTY COUNTYWIDE FIRE SERVICE DISTRICT.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. G.S. 160A-58.1(b) reads as rewritten:
7 "(b) A noncontiguous area proposed for annexation must meet all of the following
8 standards:
9 …
10 (5) The area within the proposed satellite corporate limits, when added to the area
11 within all other satellite corporate limits, may not exceed ten percent (10%)
12 of the area within the primary corporate limits of the annexing city.
13 This subdivision does not apply to the Cities of Archdale, Asheboro,
14 Belmont, Claremont, Concord, Conover, Dunn, Durham, Elizabeth City,
15 Gastonia, Greenville, Hickory, Kannapolis, King, Kings Mountain, Locust,
16 Lowell, Marion, Mount Airy, Mount Holly, New Bern, Newton, Oxford,
17 Randleman, Roanoke Rapids, Rockingham, Saluda, Sanford, Salisbury,
18 Shelby, Southport, Statesville, and Washington and the Towns of Ahoskie,
19 Angier, Apex, Ayden, Belville, Benson, Bladenboro, Bridgeton, Bunn,
20 Burgaw, Calabash, Carthage, Catawba, China Grove, Clayton, Cleveland,
21 Coats, Columbia, Columbus, Cramerton, Creswell, Dallas, Dobson, Erwin,
22 Four Oaks, Franklin, Franklinton, Franklinville, Fuquay-Varina, Garner,
23 Godwin, Goldston, Granite Quarry, Green Level, Grimesland, Harrisburg,
24 Holly Ridge, Holly Springs, Hookerton, Hope Mills, Huntersville,
25 Jamestown, Kenansville, Kenly, Knightdale, Landis, Laurel Park, Liberty,
26 Lillington, Louisburg, Madison, Maggie Valley, Maiden, Mayodan,
27 Maysville, Middlesex, Midland, Mocksville, Morrisville, Mount Pleasant,
28 Nashville, North Wilkesboro, Norwood, Oak Island, Oakboro, Ocean Isle
29 Beach, Pembroke, Pine Level, Pollocksville, Princeton, Ramseur, Ranlo,
30 Richlands, Rockwell, Rolesville, Rutherfordton, Shallotte, Siler City,
31 Smithfield, Spencer, Spring Lake, Spruce Pine, Stanley, Stem, Stovall, Surf
32 City, Swansboro, Taylorsville, Troutman, Troy, Vass, Wallace, Warsaw,
33 Watha, Waynesville, Weldon, Wendell, West Jefferson, Wilson's Mills,
34 Windsor, Wingate, Yadkinville, Youngsville, and Zebulon."
*S809-v-3*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 2.(a) The corporate limits of the Town of Rural Hall are hereby removed
2 from the Forsyth County Countywide Fire Service District.
3 SECTION 2.(b) This section has no effect upon the validity of any liens of Forsyth
4 County for ad valorem taxes outstanding before the effective date of this section.
5 SECTION 2.(c) This section becomes effective June 30, 2026. Property in the
6 territory described in this section as of January 1, 2026, is no longer subject to Forsyth County
7 Countywide Fire Service District taxes for taxes imposed for taxable years beginning on or after
8 July 1, 2026.
9 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
10 law.
